        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> I think the casting time upgrade, if there is an item (I think there is, actually, got one the other night) would really help. I mean, Cascading Darkness ... 6 damn second casting time. I still use Dooming, until I get Devouring, and I may not even use that.</P><P>As a grouping necro (only ever soloed for less than 10 levels total) a great way of erasing aggro is cast your DoT, immediately FD, wait till the tank taunts a bit, get back up. OK, the FD nerf still spanks you some, but it buys the tank a bit more time to get the thing off you. Lately, in a group which is tank heavy, I don't even use DoTs, I just use Degeneration and Crippling Claudication, I get actively sought after for these "necro buffs" as it were.</P><P>Another trick, not sure if I've mentioned it here before in another thread, when mezzing in a group, FD while it's Screaming Terror'ed, and let a tank break mez, then get up. No aggro.</P><P>Avoiding aggro in a group situation (and a raid situation) is essential, since you generally cannot fear the mob, or often root it. And if you using Ebolt /wave Root anyway :b I still don't think that AA low agro ability is really worth it for necros, with FD and all.</P><P>With our pets, the HP seem a little low compared to mage pets, although I still agree that mage pets should beat the living snot outta ours. Mages ARE their pets, if you are a necro who just uses their pet with a pet buff, you ain't playing your class, lol. We have the best DoTs in the game, and that's our speciality. So, we can be generous enough to let mages have the best pets. They don't get any decent DoTs, they have second class DDs (but still decent) and no root, snare or fear.</P><P>I hear that the 56th pet has like 1600 HP. I have also heard that the 49th pet has a hell of a lot more. I guess at later levels your pet doesn't need to tank as long, but still ... if the 56th pet had the same HP as the 49th, that might be parity. I mean, it's not meant to be balanced with the 49th pet ... it's an UPGRADE.</P><P>PS. A focussed 56th pet beats the hell outta a spectre pet :)</P><P>Saminga Daemonregina, 57th Defiler of Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.</font></td>
